On the cliffs of Miaofeng Mountain in the Mentougou District of Beijing, tiny white star-shaped flowers decorate precipices. The maple leaf clematis (Clematis acerifolia Maxim.), a species endemic to Beijing, grows only in crevices on the cliff, gaining the nickname "cliff flower." (All images via CFP) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)